labels.privacy label detail: AIM is a workload-adaptive algorithm that first selects a set of queries, then measures those queries with added noise to satisfy differential privacy, and finally generates synthetic data from the noisy measurements. It uses a set of innovative features to iteratively select the most useful measurements, reflecting both their relevance to the workload and their value in approximating the input data. We also provide analytic expressions to bound per-query error with high probability.

age.title: Age-Based Inconsistencies
age.description: These inconsistencies deal with the AGE feature; records with age-based inconsistencies might have children who are married, or infants with high school diplomas

inconsistencies.inconsistency_description: Adults ( > 14) must specify values (other than N) for all adult features
Adults needed: Family size must be at least one greater than number of children

work.title: Work-Based Inconsistencies
work.description: These inconsistencies deal with the work and finance features; records with work-based inconsistencies might have high incomes while being in poverty, or have conflicts between their industry code and industry category.

housing.title: Housing-Based Inconsistencies
housing.description: These inconsistencies deal with housing and family features; records with household-based inconsistencies might have more children in the house than the total household size, or be residents of group quarters (such as prison inmates) who are listed as owning their residences.
